ABUJA – A Federal High Court sitting in Abuja has ordered the interim forfeiture of about 10 properties and funds in banks allegedly linked to a former Governor of Zamfara State, Abdulaziz Yari. Justice Egwuatu made the order on Wednesday upon an ex-parte application filed by the Independent Corrupt Practices and other related offences Commission (ICPC). Osuobeni Ekoi Akponimisingha, moved the application on behalf of ICPC. Firm Prays Court To Nullify N80bn Chinese Rail Project Contract… Traders Drag Market Union To Market Union Over Levy It would be recalled that the Federal High Court in Abuja, had on January 26, 2021, ordered a final forfeiture of about N284, 306, 294.04 linked Abdulaziz Yari, to the Federal Government.The money was said to have been lodged in two banks. The presiding judge, Justice Ijeoma Ojukwu, held that Yari could not show how he made the huge sum of monies while or before serving as governor of the state (between May 29, 2011, and May 29, 2019). Yari and two companies belonging to him (Kayatawa Nig. Ltd and B.T. Oil and Gas Nig. Ltd) were indicted for alleged fraud and were dragged to the court by the ICPC.